5000|$|Charging {{for waste}} can also {{sometimes}} result in illegal dumping (<b>fly-tipping)</b> or the waste being passed to unlicensed or illegal disposal methods. [...] In practice, increased litter, open burning, and illegal dumping {{have not been}} observed by most pay-as-you-throw communities, especially when combined with easier recycling and composting. [...] Municipalities in Massachusetts have typically observed a reduction in trash larger than the increase in recycling, but this {{is believed to be}} due to people formerly bringing in trash from other communities (where presumably there is no free pickup) to the homes of friends and relatives.|$|E
